The paper discusses a method to optimize the evaluation of Random Forests, which is a popular classifier in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions experiments on various datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Random Forests in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE), which are also possible sub-categories.
